    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s05008t" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5049T" revno="T" date="02/12/1997">
        <title>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>3000</truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>05708</ucode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The tilt-only steering column assembly allows tilt adjustment through a lever on the left side of
                    the steering column.
                </para>
                <para>The steering wheel is connected to the tilt column assembly. The tilt column shaft is connected to
                    the lower-steering shaft with a universal joint. The lower end of the steering shaft is connected to
                    the steering gear with a second universal joint. The universal joints permit correct alignment and
                    smooth rotation of the steering shaft to steering gear with no binding of the shafts.
                </para>
                <para>The turn signal-hazard switch assembly is mounted within the main housing assembly.</para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
    </svcsection>
